===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|ply||pleat, fold}}, from {{m|frm|plier||bend, fold}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|plicō||I fold, I fold together}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|plies}}

# A [[layer]] of material.
#: {{usex|two-'''ply''' toilet paper|lang=en}}
# A [[strand]] that, twisted together with other strands, makes up [[yarn]] or [[rope]].
# {{context|colloquial|lang=en}} [[plywood|Plywood]].
# {{context|artificial intelligence|game theory|lang=en}} In two-player sequential games, a "half-turn", or one move made by one of the players.
#: ''He proposed to build Deep Purple, a super-computer capable of 24-'''ply''' look-ahead for chess.''
# {{context|now|_|chiefly|_|Scotland|lang=en}} [[state|State]], [[condition]].
#* '''1749''', John Cleland, ''Memoirs of a Woman of Pleasure'', Penguin 1985, p. 66:
#*: You may be sure, in the '''ply''' I was now taking, I had no objection to the proposal, and was rather a-tiptoe for its accomplishment.

